40|$|Previous {{research}} has found that the <b>small</b> <b>firm</b> premium which was prominent in the US and UK markets up until the late 1980 s has disappeared from both markets. In contrast, studies continue to report an exceptionally strong and persistent <b>small</b> <b>firm</b> premium over time within the Australian market. However, our analysis finds that in practice there is no exploitable <b>small</b> <b>firm</b> premium in Australian stock returns...|$|R
